Source: adic
Section: games
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Jens Thiele <karme@berlios.de>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>> 3.0.0), libsdl1.2-dev, libsdl-mixer1.2-dev, libsdl-image1.2-dev
Standards-Version: 3.5.2

Package: adic
Architecture: any
Depends: adic-data, ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: a cooperative multi-player game.
 ADIC (Any door is closed) is a cooperative multi-player game.
 The goal is to lock all the players of the other teams. 
 Main development platform is GNU/Linux - but now there are 
 cross-compiled binaries for win32.
 Beside of playing the game you can write a bot and use the game 
 as test bed for AI/robotics algorithms.
 .
 This package contains the executables.
 
Package: adic-data
Architecture: all
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: Data files for adic
 ADIC (Any door is closed) is a cooperative multi-player game.
 The goal is to lock all the players of the other teams. 
 Main development platform is GNU/Linux - but now there are 
 cross-compiled binaries for win32.
 Beside of playing the game you can write a bot and use the game 
 as test bed for AI/robotics algorithms.
 .
 This package contains the maps, graphics and sounds.
